It is heavy on the RAM limit but shouldn't really strain a mid to high level GPU. You can alleviate some of that RAM hit by just grabbing the bits that interest you rather than Complete. Obviosuly, this will mean bases won't be nearly as complex however.

I'd recommend just trying Skyways first and seeing if that suits you. Then maybe add some other packs.

Define a mid to high level GPU I have a 960 but as I said, my GFX mods seem to strain it already. Scatterer, RealPlume, EngineLighting, EVE, and a few TextuReplacer thingies.

Not a low level GPU

I would expect you to see an FPS hit with KerbinSide content on top of all that. Think of each static building as perhaps 3-4 ship parts. Then imagine having maybe 10ish buildings on the screen as well as a vessel. So you're looking at maybe 40 more ship parts making drawcalls on the GPU.

The beefier your GPU, the more drawcalls it's going to handle without sweating. The more stuff on the screen, the more drawcalls.

Changing topics for a suggestion: Being able to refuel without needing another aircraft, InfiniDice was able to run a script that made a runway support a big fuel tank that works with the static model to be able to refuel aircrafts that lands there, this way you dont need to quit playing, and reload and launch the same aircraft on another runway.

It's looking like Kerbal Konstructs, and therefore KerbinSide, isn't as compatible with the latest update as I initially thought it was. Those of you posting bug reports, I need a lot more information than I'm currently being given since I'm not seeing any of the recently reported issues.

I'll try a recompiled release of KK this week and see if it's API changes that are causing the problems.

Being able to refuel without needing another aircraft, InfiniDice was able to run a script that made a runway support a big fuel tank that works with the static model to be able to refuel aircrafts that lands there, this way you dont need to quit playing, and reload and launch the same aircraft on another runway.

There's several operational facilities accessible through the Inflight Base Boss already. That includes fuel tanks.

See the OP of the Kerbal Konstructs thread for more (slightly dated) info.
